<br>
I don't give two shits what Sony ends up SAYING the minimum system specs are, but you and I both know that minimum doesn't mean shit.<br>
<br>
I'm crazy enough to make sure I have a 7200 rpm HD, a gig of ram, a 800mhz FSB, and a 256 mb vid card to TRY eq2 out, but I don't know but maybe 3 other people that would even consider such a rediculous thing.<br>
<br>
Yeah...you'll be able to play EQ2 with 512 ram, a slower HD, a 64 (shudder) mb card, and 200 mhz FSB, I wouldn't dare try it.<br>
<br>
I want my 8x agp running across that motherboard at blazing speeds if I'm gonna bother to have a good vid card.  I want some juicy 333mhz DDR ram pumping my data.<br>
<br>
What am I getting at?  I don't think people will have a SATISFACTORY experience with EQ2 unless they upgrade their computers, and I don't think that many people will upgrade their computers JUST to play EQ2.  Catch 22 time.<br>
<br>
So in conclusion, I think EQ2 will wind up hogging too much *currently unavailable* system resources to play SMOOTHLY, and that people will stop playing unless its SO GOOD that they are willing to upgrade their PC to keep playing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeshterdaggerfury>Jeshter Daggerfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Spin Doctor <br>
